fields.inlineHelpText: This field allows you to select an Access Code that can be used to grant access to "Private" Ticket Allocations.
fields.label: Access Code
fields.name: AccessCode__c

fields.inlineHelpText: This field allows you to specify a color (either as a hexadecimal RGB code, or an HTML color name) to be used when rendering seats within this Ticket Allocation.
fields.label: Color
fields.name: Color__c

fields.inlineHelpText: The event instance with which this ticket allocation is associated.
fields.label: Event Instance
fields.name: EventInstance__c

fields.inlineHelpText: For PYOS events, this is the actual number of seats (sold or unsold) within the ticket allocation. For GA events, this is the original number of seats assigned to the ticket allocation, prior to any sales or adjustments.
fields.label: Original Quantity
fields.name: OriginalQuantity__c

fields.inlineHelpText: The current quantity of unsold seats within this ticket allocation.
fields.label: Retail Quantity
fields.name: RetailQuantity__c

fields.inlineHelpText: The status of this Ticket Allocation. Used to hold seats out of the pool of generally available seats for various purpose.
fields.label: Sale Status
fields.name: SaleStatus__c

fields.inlineHelpText: Specifies the type of seating for this Ticket Allocation.
fields.label: Seating Type
fields.name: SeatingType__c

fields.inlineHelpText: Short name for this Ticket Allocation. It should contain no whitespace.
fields.label: Short Name
fields.name: ShortName__c

fields.inlineHelpText: A lower number causes this Allocation to appear higher in the list of Allocation on the 'Select a Performance' page.
fields.label: Sort Order
fields.name: SortOrder__c

fields.inlineHelpText: Count of the number of Active Price Levels under this Allocation
fields.label: Active Levels
fields.name: ActiveLevels__c
